runs.comm: over the wicket and drifting across, takes the outside edge and runs to short third man
slightly down the leg side, deflects behind square off the pad
floated up outside off, skips outside and drills the ball into the covers
full and on middle and leg, straitening, Hales pushes it defensively to midwicket
tossed up on the stumps again, Hales sweeps hard and keeps it down, but picks out short backward square leg
full and flighted, uses the feet and pushes wide of mid-off, they have to run hard for a single
back of a length, outside off, takes the shoulder of the bat and runs wide of slip
drops short, at the body, Lumb crumps this through backward square, no one guarding out there and that's the first boundary of the innings
rolls the fingers over this, excellent cutter from Rampaul, beats Lumb outside off as he was early on the shot
big appeal, struck on the back pad, maybe a thin inside edge as Lumb pushed down the line without moving his feet. Umpire not interested and the replays show some bat involved
swings away from his body, bottom hand comes off the bat and Rampaul yells "Catch!" but it has already sailed most of the way to third man, a (streaky) bacon boundary for Lumb
tighter line on the stumps, cramps him for room - good pace too, up at 87mph
comes forward and nudges a single down the ground
tossed up and straightening outside off, Lumb waits and pushes to long-on

skips the ball on as Hales leaves his crease... got him, easy stumping! Smartly done by bowler and keeper, Badree saw Hales move early, pushed the ball through flat and quick outside off, ineffectual dab at it and it was a simple job to finish off

appeal for another stumping first ball! Wright tried to hit the cover off it, aiming down the ground and completely missing the googly, his foot was beyond the line, never really made a move back and Ramdin broke the wicket... This is going to be out as well, another failure for Wright, the crowd go barmy in Barbados! Wright didn't seem to realise the front part of his foot was only on the line, he held the pose and Ramdin just flipped off the bails
on the stumps, non-turning legbreak and Morgan goes back to defend
drops short and Morgan smartly pulls for four, rolling the wrists to send this behind square
bit of width, maybe another cutter from Rampaul, swing and miss from Lumb, who's been up the other end watching the carnage
Lumb walks down the pitch, another slower ball from Rampaul, slices it through point for a couple
drops short, pulled forcefully down into the ground but straight to midwicket
picks the slower ball this time and lofted over the covers, low risk shot as there is no one fielding out there and although it plugs in the outfield there's enough on it to dribble over the rope
tighter line, Lumb squirts a length ball through point for a single
around off stump, Morgan waits and deflects the ball to short third man, Lumb sends him back
drags this down, leg-stump line, Lumb pulls to the square-leg sweeper
reverses the hands, scooped between short third man and backward point, just over the fingertips and it races to the boundary
quick and flat, going on outside off, Morgan chops down into the covers
pushed through outside off stump again, opens the face and runs one fine of short third man
Lumb sweeps and misses, hits the thigh pad going on past the wicket, rolls past the keeper and they get one more, the throw hitting Lumb as he grounded his bat at the bowler'd end
bot of air, not really spinning, dabbed short behind square and this time they can't steal one
tossed up and breaking to off, tapped into the covers and sent back
on the stumps, gets underneath this and scoops over backward square, Morgan has strong wrists and it gets all the way to the fence
tossed up and spinning gently outside off, pushed into the covers
flatter and quicker outside off, Morgan can't get it through coming forwards
deceives him with the doosra, just as in the third ODI, only this time it bounces over the stumps
carrom ball on off stump, Morgan dead bats it back to the bowler
sliding on outside off, Lumb can't get a drive through the infield
attempts a late cut and bottom-edges into the ground and over the stumps! Straight into Ramdin's gloves, so nearly a drag on

Lumb's luck is short lived, as he pulls a half-tracker straight down the gullet of deep backward square! Third wicket for Badree, Lumb got under it rather than through the shot and it possibly held up in the wind, no drama for the catcher underneath it
dropped, though it was a reflex chance! Morgan cracked it back down the track, Badree got his hands in position but it ricocheted off the fingers
pushes forward to another legbreak that doesn't turn, thick outside edge and Narine misfields at short third man and it then escapes him on a futile chase to the boundary
tossed up, outside off, Buttler pokes it back to the bowler
the wrong'un this time, doesn't pick it and is beaten swiping off the back foot

goes for the reverse sweep and top-edge straight to the man on the edge of the circle! Buttler perishes, again he looked pretty seasick against Narine, couldn't get enough elevation on the shot and it was a simple take for short third man
tossed up full on the stumps, pokes it back
edged between keeper and slip! Placement from Bopara... or something. Tried to cut off back foot, may have been the doosra, just got enough on it to take it past Ramdin's gloves
goes back and across, opens the face to short third man
full and straight and clumped down the ground, nearly kept in at long-on but can't quite stop the ball bouncing over the rope
slightly short and wide, throws the hands through a rapier shot of the back foot, beats backward point and that's another much-needed boundary
slower ball this time, played square from the crease
fuller and straighter, nudged towards midwicket with a turn of the wrists
low full toss from Bravo and Bopara sets himself, flicks at it and only scrapes an inside edge to Ramdin's left for one
goes round the wicket, angled in towards middle and off, drops short into the covers and immediately calls his partner through
round the wicket, opens the face and runs one to short third man
goes over the wicket, worked off his pads for one into the leg side

bit of air on off stump, Morgan swats it flat towards deep midwicket... but can't clear the man! Another one bites the dust, England five down and looking like a broken-down jalopy attempting to complete the Cannonball Run. Morgan hung around to confirm the catcher hadn't stepped on to the boundary rope but he was well inside
Stokes goes back and cuts one through the off side to get off the mark first ball
drops short and this is swiped through the covers for a couple
Bopara drops behind square on the off side, wants one but Stokes turns him down
round the wicket, full at the stumps, pushed to long-on
comes down the pitch, it's a shorter delivery, Bopara aims something expansive through the off side but cloths it just wide of mid-off...the quick outfield nearly allows it to run away
chopped down to third man
short from round the wicket, Stokes pulls but the ball lobs off the splice into midwicket
this time connects well enough to clear the leg-side boundary, picks up a low full toss with plenty of bottom hand and clears deep midwicket
angled to third man
round the wicket, short, bounces more at Bopara as he pulls through square leg
swung off the bottom of the bat through midwicket
nudged off the pads into square leg
third stumping of the innings. Clueless against spin. Charges down, head in the air, swings and misses. Miles out. Some turn and bounce for Samuels, but Stokes was nowhere near the ball
worked off the pads through midwicket
pushed across outside off, cut to deep point

dropped, what a shambolic piece of cricket all round. Bresnan pulls across the line of a length ball, the top edge loops behind square on the off side and no one seems to call. Sammy ends up getting there, but can't hold on.
swings across the line of a length ball, sends it through midwicket and long-on makes a hash of the stop on the boundary
that's a lovely strike, very pleasing on the eye this time as he punches another full ball straight down the ground and beats long-on to his left
steps to leg, Rampaul landing it on a length, Bopara swings it through midwicket
short outside off, sliced down to third man and beats a fantastic diving attempt to pull off what would have been a extraordinary catch
on the pads, flicking in the air to deep midwicket
on the pads, flicked to short fine-leg
tucked into the leg side
on leg stump, Bresnan can only nudge back to the bowler
cut out to deep cover
shuffles across then sweeps this off around leg stump to short fine-leg
dropped in short, pulled off a chuncky top edge to the right of deep square
a one-handed swing across the line of a full ball on off stump...finds deep square-leg
palmed over the bar! Gayle can't quite leap high enough at cover on the edge of the ring. Bopara connected cleanly with his lofted cover drive, and just had the height

and strikes...Bopara trying to fetch this over the leg side, it's a off-cutter outside off, making Bopara reach for the ball and he can only send it high in the air. Bravo looks after the catching himself as he steadies himself around midwicket. Some exurbarant celebrations
big full toss, clubbed through midwicket
short of a length, bounces over the top edge as Broad tries to play square through point
lovely slower ball, beats Broad all ends up outside off...was giving himself room towards leg and could only poke at it
short and pulled to deep square
driven off the back foot to deep cover
touch short, cut through backward point
leg side this time, pulled to midwicket...going through the motions now
a floaty, wide delivery which spins away from Broad's flat-footed waft. Umpire checks with TV about the stumping but the foot is back
left alone outside off...Broad wanted the wide
full outside off, Bresnan almost swings himself off his feet and the thick edge flies fine of third man
low full toss outside off, swung down to long-on
length outside off, the ball scuttles underneath Broad's bat...they run a bye to the keeper
another boundary for Bresnan, this time an inside edge past the stumps and the keeper as he hoicks across the line of a length delivery
a yorker which is jabbed down the ground
a bouncer which loops off the surface, Broad is a touch early on the pull and gets it down to long-on
full outside off, swing and a miss from Broad
driven to mid-off who is inside the circle
uses his feet, whips a full delivery to short fine-leg
length delivery outside off, heaved to the left of long-on where Russell makes good ground
slower ball outside off, defeats Broad again
well, that sums up England's day! Jabbed over the top of a short ball, the ball goes through the Ramdin, Broad sets off for a run and is well short as Ramdin's throw hits direct
can't connect with a full ball outside off
that's a clean strike...another length ball which ends up in the stands, this time over deep midwicket
fuller this time, driven to deep cover
full at the stumps, gives himself some room, drives to Gayle on the edge of the circle at cover
short of a length, angled down to third man
and another run out...the ball deflected off Bresnan's boots and stopped close to the striker's crease, Tredwell was on his heels and could not beat Russell who was quick from his followthrough
drills a length ball straight down the ground...another solid swing from Bresnan
fuller, at the stumps, can't beat cover
short of a length, heaved to deep square-leg
steps to leg and reaches for a full ball, picks out Gayle at point who just about makes the stop
swings and misses
short ball outside off, slices it over backward point and it runs away for another futile boundary
